column103:
*Scenario 1: Send Completed Recredentialing Application communication to NM provider*

GIVEN that I am a Credentialing Specialist

{color:#172b4d}AND I am viewing a recredentialing case{color}

{color:#172b4d}AND the provider is associated with a Standard Office practice{color}

{color:#172b4d}AND the state associated with the recredentialing case is the state of New Mexico{color}

{color:#172b4d}WHEN the case moves into the "Ready for CVO" status{color}

THEN...
 # I see that the Completed Recredentialing App letter is automatically generated. 
 # I see that the Completed Recredentialing App letter displays the appropriate dynamic detail for the provider (i.e. name).
 # I see that the Completed Recredentialing App letter is automatically sent to the mailing address associated with the provider's primary facility.

 

*Scenario 2: Send Completed Recredentialing Application communication to provider without email*

GIVEN that I am a Credentialing Specialist

AND I am viewing a recredentialing case

AND the provider is associated with a Standard Office practice

{color:#172b4d}AND the state associated with the recredentialing case is NOT the state of New Mexico{color}

AND the Email field associated with the related provider is blank

WHEN the case moves into the "Ready for CVO" status

THEN...
 # I see that the Completed Recredentialing App letter is automatically generated. 
 # I see that the Completed Recredentialing App letter displays the appropriate dynamic detail for the provider (i.e. name).
 # I see that the Completed Recredentialing App letter is automatically sent to the mailing address associated with the provider's primary facility.

 

*Scenario 3: Completed* *Recredentialing Application* *is accessible to all users*

GIVEN that I am a System Admin or Developer

{color:#172b4d}AND I am viewing a recredentialing case{color}

{color:#172b4d}AND the provider is associated with a Standard Office practice{color}

{color:#172b4d}AND the state associated with the recredentialing case is the state of New Mexico{color}

{color:#172b4d}WHEN the case moves into the "Ready for CVO" status{color}

THEN...
 # I see that the Completed Recredentialing App letter is linked to the Provider's account in Salesforce, and can be can be viewed/downloaded as needed by all Salesforce users.

